        <abstract>
            <p>Thanks for reply to queries.</p> 
<p>Requests that a wild rock-pigeon be sent. Have they been domesticated as William Macgillivray says [<hi rend="italic">History of British birds</hi> (1837) 1: 275–84; see also <hi rend="italic">Variation</hi> 1: 185n.]?</p> 
            <p>Is rabbit wild in Shetlands?</p>
            <p>LE’s information on drifted trees adds an archipelago to his list.</p>
            <p>Requests information on variation in domesticated Shetland animals;</p>
            <p>bones of large quadrupeds in peat.</p>
        </abstract>
